globalProps.text: Tips for making an exceptional table tent design

globalProps.title: Pick the right size for maximum impact
globalProps.alt: Pick the right size for maximum impact

globalProps.text: Pick the right size for maximum impact
Your table tent should fit the space to ensure the message is clearly visible. A 4 × 6 inches size is ideal for tight spaces like cafés or bar counters.

In busier spots like restaurants or hotel lobbies, a larger table tent such as 5.5 × 8.5 inches or a full-page size of 8.5 × 11 inches can make your message stand out. Pick the size that suits your setting.

globalProps.title: Choose the style that best delivers messages
globalProps.alt: Choose the style that best delivers messages

globalProps.text: Choose the style that best delivers messages
Table tents aren’t just for show; they’re your message. Go for an A-frame style if you need extra space to show multiple products or want your message seen from every angle.
For something simple and space-saving, opt for a single-panel layout. It's easy to print and fold, and also more suitable for focused messages. Make your brand stand out with the right style!

globalProps.title: Add custom designs to instantly draw attention
globalProps.alt: Add custom designs to instantly draw attention

globalProps.text: Add custom designs to instantly draw attention
People naturally look at the top first, so placing your logo at the top left or center is a smart way to make a strong first impression.

Just below the logo, you can center a large, eye-catching image that shows off what you’re offering, like a tasty dish, a great product, or a nice space. Then, wrap it up with a catchy slogan or quote that inspires action.

globalProps.title: Use suitable colors that reflect your brand
globalProps.alt: Use suitable colors that reflect your brand

globalProps.text: Use suitable colors that reflect your brand
If you’re designing a table tent for a business or finance brand, use white or blue for the background, white for the text, and gray for the borders to keep it neat and professional.
But if it’s for eco-friendly or handmade products, kraft brown makes a great natural base. Pair it with green headers and cream text for an earthy feel that really fits the vibe.

dataList.question: How do I choose the right material for my table tent design?
dataList.answer: Simply pick the one that best fits your design goal and style. If your design includes bright colors, images, or fine text, white cardboard is the best choice. It keeps everything sharp and vibrant. For a simple, eco-friendly look, kraft paper offers a natural, rustic feel that works great with minimalist designs. You can also consider coated papers for a polished finish, or acrylic for a sleek, modern look.

dataList.question: How can I ensure my table tent design looks more authentic?
dataList.answer: Start by choosing the right table tent mockup from our gallery. Customize to own every detail, from the material to color and branding, to make your design feel more genuine. Ensure a minimalist design with bold, stylish, easy-to-read fonts. More importantly, place your table tent mockup against real backdrops like on a cafe counter or restaurant table to make it feel relatable.
